I have just finished watching report on RTE1 News on TV about the poor two
17 year old's killed in the car crash in Roscommon at 2am in the morning. I
have a couple of comments:

For a start I was appalled that they have a Garda talking to the news who
seemed inappropriate who sounded quite jolly and almost looked like he was
going to laugh or something rather than some Garda that would show
compassion.... and not look so happy. I am sure the Garda in question is a
very nice and friendly man but in this situation you have to have someone
that shows a bit of compassion I think.

another comment what were 17 year olds doing out driving on the roads at 2am
in the morning for anyway especially weekday? and 4 17 year olds in the car
and that time in the morning, I know I shouldn't tar them all with the same
brush but you know teenagers all in a car are like with egging the driver to
go faster.

However, the Priest that was interviewed afterwards would have you believe
that the road they were travelling on was 'substandard' and dangerous and
that there have been other crashes there - but even if some people get onto
a substandard road if you drive on that road too fast you are going to leave
it .

I don't want to speed ill of the dead and my thoughts are with the teenagers
family but these poor kids with their life just starting out when is someone
going to stand up and really do something about not just making the roads /
road conditions great in Ireland when is someone going to tackle the issue
of teenagers out late at night and speeding (quite possibly drinking as well
maybe) and leaving the roads like this-  its happening too often and too
many teenagers are losing their lives over it.

Andy.
